word_mean_info__list.difference: 非正式用词，侧重在一类中唯一无可匹敌、无与伦比的特征。
语气较强，强调仅此一个，再无第二个。
普通用词，常可与sole换用，但侧重仅限于指定的人或物，而不需要更多。
着重专指某人或某物，而不是别的。
语气强于only，指仅有一个或一群，只考虑这一个或这一群。

bilingual.target: 马克斯韦尔是一个独特的姓氏。

bilingual.source: Each country has its own unique culture.
bilingual.target: 每个国家都有自己独特的文化。

bilingual.source: I was totally unprepared for its unique beauty.
bilingual.target: 我完全没有准备好迎接它独特的美。

bilingual.source: Every festival has its different customs and unique charms.
bilingual.target: 每个节日都有其不同的习俗和独特的魅力。

bilingual.source: The stores in the Chinatown offer a unique range of souvenirs.
bilingual.target: 唐人街的商店提供独特的纪念品。
他有一种独特的性感魅力。
肉桂有一种独特的香味。

list.abstract: Lenka来自澳洲Electronic-Rock团体Decoder Ring中的优质创作甜美女歌手，动员Stuart Brawley、Pierre Marchand、Mike Elizondo、John Alagia、Jason Lader等五位当红制作人联手打造。

yingyinNormal.en: When we performed your operation we found something very unique. One of a kind, actually.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们给你手术时发现了非常独特的事，独一无二。

yingyinNormal.en: Humans consider themselves unique, so they rooted their whole theory of existence on their uniqueness.
yingyinNormal.zh: 人类总以为自己是独特的，存在理论总是以独特性为基础。

yingyinNormal.en: I see hope. I see a unique voice who's learned to appreciate the influence of hope. Try not to lose that. I won't.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我看到了希望，我看到了一个独特的声音，她学会了欣赏希望的影响，不要丢了这一点。我不会、

yingyinNormal.en: Besides, these kinds of books are always so boring, so safe. I want something different, something unique. Your voice.
yingyinNormal.zh: 再说，这种书都很无聊，太保守，我想要点不同的，独特的，用你的文笔。

yingyinNormal.en: Denied enlistment due to poor health, Steven Rogers was chosen for a program unique in the annals of American warfare.
yingyinNormal.zh: 由于身体孱弱，被军队拒绝后，史蒂夫罗杰斯被美国战争史上一个独特的项目选中。

yingyinNormal.en: I don't want to kill Ultron. He's unique. And he's in pain. But that pain will roll over the earth, so he must be destroyed.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我并不想杀死奥创，他是独特的，而且很痛苦，但他的痛苦会毁灭地球，所以他必须被摧毁。

yingyinNormal.en: Space travel has been a staple of the movies from the very beginning, but the feature film Interstellar has a unique pedigree.
yingyinNormal.zh: 从最开始，太空旅行就成为电影的主题但故事片《星际穿越》有独特的背景。

yingyinNormal.en: What are the odds that two individuals as unique as ourselves would be connected by someone as comparatively workaday as your son?
yingyinNormal.zh: 像我们这么独特的两个人通过像你儿子这样的庸人而联系上的几率有多大？

yingyinNormal.en: It was the result of a unique approach to life I believe almost anybody can adopt. It starts with embracing reality and dealing with it.
yingyinNormal.zh: 而是因为独特的处事方式，我相信任何人都能学会。我们要从拥抱和处理现实开始。

yingyinNormal.en: On this remote American island, the unique Polynesian culture of the Hawaiians, and their special connection to nature, is ever present.
yingyinNormal.zh: 在这个偏远的美国岛屿，有着夏威夷独特的波利尼西亚文化，以及它们与大自然之间，永存的特殊联系。

yingyinNormal.en: So successful, it's become a unique attraction in its own right, and now draws visitors from as far and wide as Beijing, 875 miles away.
yingyinNormal.zh: 如此蒸蒸日上，这个人造沙滩本身也成为了一道独特的风景线。如今它吸引着从一千四百多公里外的北京千里迢迢而来的游客。

yingyinNormal.en: Our role is simple. Through our ecosystem, we help merchants and customers find each other and conduct business on their terms and in ways that best serve their unique needs.
yingyinNormal.zh: 其实，我们的目标非常简单，通过阿里巴巴搭建的生态系统，能够帮助商家和客户找到彼此，并且按照他们独特的需求方式开展业务。

yingyinNormal.en: What is it about the word "unique" you don't understand?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你对独一无二这个词很难理解么？

yingyinNormal.en: This approach led me to create a company with the unique idea meritocracy, operating in a unique way, that produced unique successes.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这让我创建了一家任人唯贤的公司，运营方式独特，成功也很独特。

yingyinNormal.en: This is an effort that America has the unique ability to lead.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这是美国完全有能力领导的行动。

yingyinNormal.en: Yes, really one resource in particular. One unique to our planet. Us.
yingyinNormal.zh: 是的，确切的说是一种特别的资源，地球特有的。我们。

yingyinNormal.en: The kind of unique asset that no government would ever admit to employing.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他就是那种特别的资产，所有政府都不会承认曾经雇佣过他。

yingyinNormal.en: It's called double fertilization, and it's unique to the seeds of flowers.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这叫做双受精，只有开花植物的种子拥有这种机制。

yingyinNormal.en: This is gonna take someone with a very unique set of skills. This is gonna take…
yingyinNormal.zh: 需要一个拥有一身独特技能的人，需要一个…

yingyinNormal.en: There's always something to be learned. Because every situation on the road is unique? Yes.
yingyinNormal.zh: 总有些新的东西要学习。因为路面上的状况是瞬息万变的，对吗？是的。

examination_example.sentence: The Eisenhower Executive Office Building commands a <highlight>unique</highlight> position in both the national history and the architectural heritage of the United States.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 艾森豪威尔行政大楼在美国国家历史和建筑遗产中都占有独特的地位。

examination_example.sentence: The study is a genome-wide analysis conducted on 1, 932 <highlight>unique</highlight> subjects which compared pairs of unrelated friends and unrelated strangers.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这项研究是对1932名独特的受试者进行的全基因组分析，比较了几对不相关的朋友和不相关的陌生人。

examination_example.sentence: It is far better to spend money on experiences, like interesting trips, <highlight>unique</highlight> meals or even going to the cinema.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 把钱花在体验上要好得多，比如有趣的旅行、独特的美食甚至去看电影。

word_usage.usage: unique意为“独一无二的”，带有赞许的含义；而它的近义词special意为“特殊的，特别的”，则为中性词。

examination_example.sentence: If you want to reduce boredom and increase your sense of meaning, seek work where you can make a <highlight>unique</highlight> contribution.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如果你想减少无聊感，增加你的存在意义，那就找一份你能做出独特贡献的工作。

examination_example.sentence: Schools see young people more than any other service, which gives them a <highlight>unique</highlight> ability get to children and young people.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 学校比其他任何公共部门都更多地关注年轻人，这给了他们一种独特的能力去接触孩子和年轻人。

examination_example.sentence: In a 2011 USPS case study, the agency emphasized its massive infrastructure as a "<highlight>unique</highlight> federal asset" to be called upon in a disaster or terrorist attack.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在2011年美国邮政的一份案例研究中，该机构强调其庞大的基础设施是在灾难或恐怖袭击中需要调用的一份“独特的联邦资产。”

examination_example.sentence: C) It is a <highlight>unique</highlight> trait specific to the human race.
The ants' method of staying cool is <highlight>unique</highlight> among animals.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 蚂蚁保持凉爽的方法在动物中是独一无二的。

examination_example.sentence: "I think we're <highlight>unique</highlight> as a federal agency," USPS official Mike Swig art told me, "be use we're in literally every community in this country.... We're obligated to deliver to that point on a daily basis."
examination_example.sentence_trans: 美国邮政局官员迈克·斯威特跟我这么说：“我认为我们作为一个联邦机构是独一无二的，因为我们几乎忙活在国家的每一个社区里...我们有义务每天都做到这一点。”

direction_info.description:

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2015-2022年8年间全国卷和自主命题省市高考卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: Komodo National Park, officially recognized in, is popular for ecotourism because of its <highlight>unique</highlight> biodiversity.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 官方认可的科莫多国家公园因其独特的生物多样性而受到生态旅游业的欢迎。

examination_example.sentence: These patterns are <highlight>unique</highlight> to each person.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这些图案对每个人来说都是独一无二的。

examination_example.sentence: Frequent stops are made for photo taking as your guide offers <highlight>unique</highlight> facts and history.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当你的导游讲解独特的事实和历史时，你可以经常停下来拍照。

examination_example.sentence: The product，though <highlight>unique</highlight> (独特的) at the time，was expensive and heavy; besides，some of its most important features (特点) didn't work properly.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 该产品虽然在当时是独一无二的，但价格昂贵且笨重。 此外，它的一些最重要的功能无法正常工作。

examination_example.sentence: Living in a village provides him with <highlight>unique</highlight> experiences，quite different from busy life in big cities，such as Shanghai，where he studies.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 乡村生活为他提供了独特的体验，与他就读的上海等大城市的忙碌生活截然不同。

examination_example.sentence: The patterns look similar，but they are <highlight>unique</highlight> like humans' fingerprints (指纹).
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这些图案看起来相似，但它们像人类的指纹一样独特
